                     <p> 
                        <pb n="46"/> 
                  HATTON near DERESBURY. <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Hatton</surname>
                        </persName>, 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Stephen</forename> 
                           <surname>Sompnor</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111022">Leigh near Acton Brygge</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
                  and <persName>
                           <forename>Hugh</forename> 
                           <surname>Colstanehok</surname>, clerk</persName>, grant to
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Peter</forename> 
                           <surname>Hatton</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111017">Hatton</placeName>
                        </persName>
                  their capital messuage in <placeName key="place_111017">Hatton near Deresbury</placeName> with all other messuages &amp;c. in the village 
                  and territory of Hatton, to hold the same to him for his life with remainder to his sons. Also they appoint 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> 
                           <surname>Grymesdych</surname> near <placeName role="person" key="place_111028">Norcoot</placeName>
                        </persName>
                  and <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Hatton</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111013">Crooton</placeName>
                        </persName> 
                  to give seisin of the same. 
                  Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_111017">Hatton</placeName>, 9 Dec., <origDate notBefore="1486-08-22" notAfter="1487-08-21">2 Hen. VII</origDate>. 
                  . </p>
                  </msItem>
